definitions: To manage to see or hear something with difficulty.
To deal with a situation, usually successfully.
To write out or complete a form or document.
To kiss and touch in a sexual way.
To pretend or claim something, often falsely.
examples: I can't make out what she's saying.
How did you make out on your exam?
Please make out the check to 'Cash'.
They were making out in the back row of the cinema.
He tried to make out that he was sick.
